r felt so special forTommy Fleetwood.\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 468, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9918839592872217, \"rank\": 0.008182420904313077, \"text\": \"Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 408}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 33-year-old has made an unwanted habit ofnearly-but-not quite finishesat majors and another runners-up spot was the ultimate outcome atLe Golf Nationalas he fellagonisingly short of his golden Olympic ambitions.\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golf\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8676476104478375e-22, \"text\": \"Golf\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golf\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an unwanted habit\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 522}, {\"ngram\": \"-not quite finishesat majors\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 563}, {\"ngram\": \"another runners-up spot\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 591}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate outcome\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 616}, {\"ngram\": \"his golden Olympic ambitions\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time, however, there was a consolation prize of sorts.Fleetwood is never happy to settle for second bestbut leaving Paris with a silver medal having gone toe-to-toe with a who's who of modern greats over a captivating final day gave him plenty to be proud of.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3756152918733956e